{@--3@} (In <ls>Mīm.</ls> <ab>phil.</ab>) Exclusion,
specification, limitation to that which
is enumerated or expressly 
mentioned, so that everything else is
excluded; ({#parisaMKyA#} is opposed to
{#viDi#} which lays down a rule for the
first time, and to {#niyama#} which restricts
the choice to an alternative which
is expressly stated when several
such alternatives are possible);  
{#viDiratyaMtamaprAptO niyamaH pAkzike sati .#} 
{#tatra cAnyatra ca prAptO parisaMKyeti#} 
{#gIyate ..#} {%<ab>e. g.</ab>%} {#paMca paMcanaKA BakzyAH#} 
usually quoted by the Mīmāṃsakas;
{#ayaM niyamaviDirna tu parisaMKyA#} <ls>Kull.</ls>
on <ls>Ms. 3. 45.</ls>
